HEADWORD: Myrtiform
<hw>Myr"ti*form</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>myrtus</ets> myrtle + <ets>-form</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>myrtiforme</ets>.]</ety> <def>Resembling myrtle or myrtle berries;
